# Phase 7: Presentation Settings Redesign and Presets Management

This phase introduces a robust Preset management system and completely overhauls the Presentation Settings UI layout.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Since we are adding fundamentally new fields (`presetName`, `aspectRatio`, `isTransparent`) to the `PresentationSettings` data model, this will require running `build_runner` to generate the new Isar database schemas. Existing Isar data may be reset depending on how Isar handles the ID transition from a fixed singleton `id = 1` to `id = Isar.autoIncrement`.
> - Please confirm the logic for the "Active Preset": Should clicking on a Preset button in the "Choose Preset" list immediately activate it for the Live Projector, or does navigating into the Edit screen just allow you to modify it while an explicit "Set Active" mechanism is provided later? (For this plan, I assume opening a preset to Edit also makes it the previewed/active preset for now).

## Proposed Changes

---
### Database & Data Models

#### [MODIFY] [presentation_settings.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/settings/data/presentation_settings.dart)
- Remove `Id id = 1;` and replace with `Id id = Isar.autoIncrement;` to allow storing multiple presets.
- Add `String presetName = 'Default';`
- Add `bool isDefault = false;` to explicitly identify the non-deletable base preset.
- Add fields for Aspect Ratio:
  - `String aspectRatio = '16:9';`
  - `double customWidth = 1920.0;`
  - `double customHeight = 1080.0;`
- Add field for background transparency logic:
  - `bool isTransparent = false;`
- Ensure a default fallback preset is seeded into the Isar database if none exist on startup.

#### [NEW] [presentation_settings.g.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/settings/data/presentation_settings.g.dart)
- Will automatically be re-generated via `build_runner` due to schema changes.

