## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Open up KeryxPro and navigate to Settings -> Presentation Settings.
2. Verify that it says "Choose Preset" and "Default" is present.
3. Test creating a new preset named "Worship Sunday" and verify it renders next to "Default".
4. Click the newly created preset.
5. Verify the Dialog switches flawlessly into Edit Mode. The title bar should show `< Worship Sunday`, `Song`, and `Scripture`.
6. Tweak Aspect Ratio (Select Custom, enter W/H values) and observe preview dimension changes.
7. Switch between Transparent/Background Color explicitly confirming they act mutually exclusively.
8. Verify that Left preview container reflects the respective background state actively.
9. Check the right half simply reflects structurally ready empty blocks for next phase.
